# prototype

**Instance Property**

The prototype cell that’s copied whenever the matrix creates a new cell.

## Declaration

```swift
@NSCopying @MainActor var prototype: NSCell? { get set }
```

## Discussion

When the value of this property is `nil`, there is no prototype cell.

## Related Documentation

- **init(frame:mode:prototype:numberOfRows:numberOfColumns:)**: Initializes and returns a newly allocated matrix of the specified size using the given cell as a prototype.
- **makeCell(atRow:column:)**: Creates a new cell at the location specified by the given row and column in the receiver.

## Managing the Cell Class

- **cellClass**: The subclass of [doc://com.apple.appkit/documentation/AppKit/NSCell] that the matrix uses when creating new (empty) cells.
